<recipe>
<title>
Lentil Bolognese
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
COOK TIME: 30 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 45 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: gluten free, lentil, vegan
SERVINGS: 10 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="2.0 Tablespoon">Olive Oil</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0">Onion</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0">Celery</ingredient><ingredient amount="3.0">Carrot</ingredient><ingredient amount="7.0">Garlic</ingredient><ingredient amount="6.0 Ounce">Tomato Paste</ingredient><ingredient amount="15.0 Ounce">Tomato Sauce</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 Ounce">Tomato</ingredient><ingredient amount="">Pepper</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Add onion, celery, and carrot.
Cook, stirring as needed, until softened, about 5-10 minutes.
Add garlic, and cook, stirring frequently, for 30 seconds.
Stir in tomato paste, and cook, stirring it in, for 1 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, diced tomatoes with juice, basil, oregano, baking soda, and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in lentils and water.
Simmer, stirring regularly, until lentils have softened, about 20-30 minutes.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>